<dl id="n12078f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12078f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12078f"> 78(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> O felix culpa! <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12078f"><li>FW 536.08f </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/lexrB.htm#n12078f">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/l39rB.htm#n12078f">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12078f">MS BL 47484a-35</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:129 <a name="rAd3" href="../../FF/fdra/rda.htm#rBd3">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/rB/rBd3.htm#n12078f">Draft: III&sect;3B.3</a> </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: L. <i><mark>O felix culpa</mark></i>. O happy fault. (This derives from the <i>Exsultet</i>, which is sung by the deacon before the Pascal Candle on Easter Night. The full passage reads: <i>O felix culpa, quae talem ac tantum meruit habere Redemptorem!</i> [O happy fault that merited so great a Redeemer!] ) </mm> </dd></dl>
